unchangedJobs.description:
Sustainability is a key element within our business, it is pivotal in ensuring that our business is future proof for all actors in our supply chains. We have a temporary role (April ’26 –February ’27) available to cover the maternity leave of the sustainability coordinators of the Baronie. The scope of the role is Baronie with specific emphasis on Germany, Poland, Switzerland and Belgium.
In your role, youwill report to our Head of Sustainability and work closely together with the other members of the sustainability team based in Europe and Cote d’Ivoire. You will be part of the international sustainability team of the group, our internal and external ambassador for a diversity of sustainability topics. After your introduction period you will be responsible for the proactive implementation of our sustainability activities. As this is a temporary role it is important that you are able to connect in a relative short time with the relevant internal and external stakeholders of the Baronie. The role will be based at our office in Caslano (Switzerland) or in Norderstedt (Germany).

## Your key responsibilities
- First point of contact for internal and external stakeholders of several of our entities on sustainability topics;
- Fulfilling customer and stakeholder requests on a diversity of sustainability topics;
- Working closely with relevant colleagues and stakeholders to ensure compliance with national and international sustainability related legislations and due diligence; with emphasis on the EUDR implementation by end of 2026;
- Conclude the scope 1, 2 and 3 CO2 assessment of the Group.
- Pro-active internal and external promotion of the Group’s sustainable cocoa program ‘Transparence Cacao’;
- Contribute to Group sustainability topics and periodical reporting to Group level with requested updates;
- Monitoring & evaluation: Collect, analyse and validate sustainability data for internal and external reporting;
- Assisting with internal and external sustainability related communication;
- Taking a collaborative, connecting and active role within our organization;

## Your skill & expertise
- You are fluent in German and English. This is a must-have. Any other languages such as French would be an advantage;
- A completed Bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline to the role (e.g. (food) sustainability, environment);
- Experience in a similar or relevant role within the food/commodity industry is preferred but we are open for a young graduate with an affinity for sustainability related topics such as environment, due diligence, human rights;
- You combine technical skills (data management and analysis) with strong functional skills (communication and project management);
- Knowledge of and experience with the implementation of national and international regulations related to sustainability, due diligence and/ or climate;
- A pragmatic personality with a broad interest, high sense of ownership, entrepreneurial work ethic, hands-on mentality, excellent interpersonal skills and a flexible, solution-driven mind-set;
- You have a structured way of working and enjoy working both independently and in a team;
- Proficient computer skills (Office package);
- Excellent communication skills, across all levels of our organisation, both verbal and written, are crucial elements of your profile;

## As a Sustainability Coordinator (Maternity leave cover) we offer you
- Full time, diverse and challenging role in a growing international group;
- International exposure to implement the sustainability strategy within our company;
- An entrepreneurial company culture which offers you a lot of autonomy and values initiative;
- A good remuneration package;
- Training and career opportunities.

